	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Okee dokee, so I answered my own question last time, but this time, not so much  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> 
<br />
<br />I've been reading up on Castlevania III and the long and winding road folks have followed to run it with their PowerPaks.  I got the Japanese version to run just fine, but the music doesn't play correctly and I really don't want to have to solder anything.
<br />
<br />I've read that if I replace mm5 (I'm guessing that's Map05) it runs pretty well.  I was curious if anyone has had success with this method, and if so, do it affect anything other games?
<br />
<br />Thank you so much <img src="./images/smilies/icon_exclaim.gif" alt=":!:" title="Exclamation" />

		

		</td>
